trend_summary: Across the image series, the corridor remains mainly forest-dominated with scattered farms. Minor housing clusters and a small industrial pad form along the main road, while several fields expand and a few clear-cuts re-green. Overall change is modest; the landscape stays low-density and predominantly rural.
notable_changes: Incremental residential infill around the central road junction.
Enlargement of farmland plots in the western and central zones.
Emergence of a small industrial/storage pad near the eastern edge.
Visible regrowth of forest on earlier clear-cut patches, especially south-central areas.
Slight widening and brightening of the main east-west highway, indicating surfacing upgrades.
